{{see|anne}}

==English==

===Etymology 1===
From the French ''[[#French|Anna]]'' < Greek [[Άννα]]. [[Anna]] is the Greek form of the Hebrew female name [[חנה|חַנָּה]] ([[Hannah]]), meaning 'grace; gracious'. Cf. [[Johannes]], [[Hannibal]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æn|-æn]]

===Proper noun===
'''Anne'''
# A female [[given name]].

===Etymology 2===
A shortened form of any of various Germanic masculine names which began with ''arn'' (''eagle''), such as [[Arnold]].

===Proper noun===
'''Anne'''
# A [[male]] [[given name]].

